BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:k_hO8lv8ZyJR9t9jKXLyu
SUMMARY:IMPROV 100 ISSAQUAH - Intro to Improv: Say Yes!\\\, SPRING '26
DTSTAMP:20260405T040311Z
DTSTART:20260420T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Discover improv in Issaquah. Build confidence\\\, meet new peop
	le\\\, and learn to create stories through fun\\\, supportive games and sc
	ene work.\\n\\n\\n\\nLooking for a fun\\\, fresh way to connect with other
	s\\\, spark creativity\\\, and step out of the everyday routine? Welcome t
	o Intro to Improv at Unexpected Productions Improv School Eastside in Issa
	quah. Whether you are a working professional hoping to improve communicati
	on\\\, a creative soul searching for a new outlet\\\, or someone simply wa
	nting more laughter and community in your week\\\, this class is the perfe
	ct place to begin. \\nIn this beginner-friendly course\\\, you will learn 
	the foundational skills of improvisation: active listening\\\, collaborati
	on\\\, spontaneity\\\, and using your own life experiences to create hones
	t\\\, engaging scenes and stories. Improv is not about being funny\\\, it 
	is about being present\\\, supportive\\\, and open. And yes\\\, along the 
	way\\\, you will laugh more than you have in ages. \\nOur community values
	 connection and growth\\\, and this class is built on those principles. Yo
	u will work in a supportive group where the guiding philosophy is simple: 
	When your scene partner looks good\\\, you look good. Together\\\, we buil
	d trust\\\, confidence\\\, and creativity\\\, one scene at a time. \\n\\nU
	nder the guidance of our experienced faculty\\\, you will learn to:\\nBe a
	 better listener\\nConquer fears and build confidence\\nSpark creativity\\
	nMeet new people and make real connections\\nBecome a better problem solve
	r\\nSay yes more in your life\\nStep out of your comfort zone\\nImprove pu
	blic speaking\\nFail easier (and laugh about it)\\nDiscover more about you
	rself\\nHave an absolute blast\\n\\nThis class includes lots of laughter\\
	\, lots of stage time\\\, and zero pressure. Every student begins here. No
	 experience needed. Just bring curiosity and a willingness to try somethin
	g new. \\nUnexpected Productions Improv School is thrilled to bring our ne
	west Eastside improv classes to Issaquah\\\, serving the communities of th
	e Sammamish Plateau\\\, East Renton\\\, Bellevue\\\, Snoqualmie Valley\\\,
	 and beyond. \\nClass Details\\nDates: Six (8) Monday classes \\nTime: 7:0
	0pm to 9:00pm \\nLocation: Improv School Eastside Issaquah \\n1315 NW Mall
	 Street\\\, Suite 4 Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslamp Bar & Grill
	) \\nMaximum students: 16 \\nAges: 18 plus \\nCost: $320 \\nPrerequisite: 
	None \\nNote: Attendance at the first session is mandatory\\\, as it sets 
	the tone and foundation for the entire quarter. If you know you will miss 
	the first class\\\, please register for a future session.\n\nhttps://www.u
	nexpectedproductions.org/event/intro-to-improv-eastside-issaquah-mondays/\
	n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/intro-to-improv-eastside-is
	saquah-mondays/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:_5AjVlQNLuXRXvxWbR2lE
SUMMARY:Improv Level Up: Turn Games into Scene Magic with Alan Hawkins - Is
	saquah
DTSTAMP:20260405T040311Z
DTSTART:20260421T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Many improvisers begin with short-form games\\\, but hidden ins
	ide those fast\\\, playful formats are powerful tools for deeper scene wor
	k. In this four-week class\\\, we’ll explore how the instincts you already
	 use in games can strengthen your long-form improvisation. By unpacking th
	e mechanics behind classic games\\\, you’ll learn how to build stronger sc
	enes\\\, develop clearer relationships\\\, and create more confident impro
	vised storytelling. \\nThrough energetic exercises and supportive coaching
	\\\, you’ll discover how skills like listening\\\, commitment\\\, pattern 
	recognition\\\, and emotional connection can expand beyond the game struct
	ure and fuel longer\\\, richer scenes. If you’ve ever wondered how to brid
	ge the gap between short-form fun and long-form storytelling\\\, this clas
	s will help you make that leap. \\nClass Details\\nDates: Four (4) Tuesday
	s \\nTime: 7:00 pm–9:00 pm \\nLocation: Unexpected Productions – Issaquah 
	\\n1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (next to the 
	Gaslamp Bar and Grill) \\nMaximum Students: 16 \\nCost: $270 \\nPrerequisi
	te: Any Improv Class or Experience \\nMeet Your Instructor: Alan Hawkins\\
	nAlan Hawkins is an improviser from Los Angeles and Chicago with over two 
	decades of performance and teaching experience. A graduate of The Second C
	ity Conservatory\\\, The Second City Musical Conservatory\\\, iO West\\\, 
	Comedysportz Chicago\\\, and The Annoyance\\\, Alan has performed across t
	he U.S. and internationally with the acclaimed trio Extra Shelves and as a
	 guest with Grand Theft Improv in London. He has taught and directed for n
	umerous programs\\\, including the Teen Comedy Festival in Chicago. \\nAla
	n is an ensemble member of Unexpected Productions—America’s longest-runnin
	g Theatresports company—and the author of “YOU CAN’T LEARN IMPROV FROM A B
	OOK.” His classes are known for being energetic\\\, supportive\\\, and dee
	ply fun. \\nWhat to Bring\\nThis class involves movement\\\, so please dre
	ss comfortably and bring a bottle of water. \\nCancellation Policy\\nWe ar
	e unable to offer refunds.\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/
	theatrical-styles-with-alan-hawkins-issaquah-2/\n\nFrom Unexpected Product
	ions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/theatrical-styles-with-alan
	-hawkins-issaquah-2/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
